{"parse":{"title":"pear","pageid":14446,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n{{rfquote|en}}\n{{wp|<dab>}}\n[[Image:Pears.jpg|thumb|Photo of a pair of '''pears''' on a tree]]\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|en|:inh|enm:pere<id:pear>|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|pere}}, from {{inh|en|ang|pere}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*peru}}, from {{der|en|la-vul|pira}}, originally the plural of {{der|en|la|pirum}} but reconstrued as a feminine singular, ultimately a loanword from an unknown Mediterranean {{der|en|qfa-sub|-}} source. \n\nCognate with {{cog|sco|peer||pear}}, {{cog|stq|Peere}}, {{m|stq|Pere||pear}}, {{cog|fy|par||pear}}, {{cog|nl|peer||pear}}, {{cog|da|-}}, {{cog|kl|-}}, {{cog|nb|-}}, {{cog|nn|pære||pear}}, {{cog|fo|-}}, {{cog|is|pera||pear}}, {{cog|sv|päron||pear}}, {{cog|de|Birne||pear}}, {{cog|lb|Bier}}, {{m|lb|Bir||pear}}, {{cog|wym|biyn||pear}}, {{cog|yi|באַר||pear}}, {{cog|fr|poire||pear}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/pɛə/|a=RP}}\n* {{IPA|en|/pɛː/|a=SSB}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-pear.ogg|a=UK|IPA=[pʰɛː]}}\n* {{enPR|pâr|a=GenAm}}, {{IPA|en|/pɛɹ/}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-pear.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{IPA|en|/peː/|a=AU}}\n** {{audio|en|en-au-pair.ogg|a=AU}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈpeə/|a=NZ,non-near-square}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈpiə/|a=NZ,near-square}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈpeɹ/|a=Scotland}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈpiːə(r)/|a=InE}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈpɜː(ɹ)/|a=Lancashire,square-nurse}}\n* {{homophones|en|pair|pare|pere|;|peer|pier<aa:both <<near-square>>>|;|per|purr<aa:both <<square-nurse>>>}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɛə(ɹ)|s=1}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n{{wp}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q13099586}}An edible fruit produced by the pear tree, similar to an [[apple]] but typically elongated towards the stem.\n# {{senseid|en|Q146281}}A type of fruit tree ({{taxfmt|Pyrus communis|species}}).\n#: {{syn|en|pear tree}}\n# The wood of the pear tree ([[pearwood]], [[pear wood]]).\n# [[choke pear|Choke pear]] (a [[torture]] device).\n# {{lb|en|Jamaica}} [[avocado]], [[alligator pear]]\n# A desaturated [[chartreuse]] yellow [[colour]], like that of a pear.\n#: {{color panel|D1E231}}\n\n====Hypernyms====\n* {{sense|edible fruit}} [[Thesaurus:fruit|fruit]], {{l|en|pome}}\n\n====Hyponyms====\n{{col3|en|title=edible fruit <u>or</u> type of fruit tree\n|African pear|[[anchovy pear]] ({{taxlink|Grias cauliflora|species}})|[[apple pear]] ({{taxfmt|Pyrus pyrifolia|species}})|[[Asian pear]] ({{taxfmt|Pyrus pyrifolia|species}})\n|[[balsam pear]] ({{taxfmt|Momordica charantia|species}}, {{taxfmt|Citrullus lanatus|species}})|Bradford pear|butter pear\n|[[cactus pear]] ({{taxfmt|Opuntia|genus}} spp.)|[[Callery pear]] ({{taxlink|Pyrus calleryana|species}})|[[Chinese pear]] ({{taxfmt|Pyrus pyrifolia|species}})|[[Chinese white pear]] ({{taxlink|Pyrus × bretschneideri|nothospecies}})|choke pear|{{vern|common pear}} ({{taxfmt|Pyrus communis|species}})\n|{{vern|European pear}} ({{taxfmt|Pyrus communis|species}})\n|[[garlic pear]] ({{taxfmt|Crateva|genus}} spp.)|{{vern|grape pear}} ({{taxfmt|Amelanchier canadensis|species}})\n|{{vern|hard pear}} ({{taxlink|Olinia ventosa|species}})\n|[[Japanese pear]] ({{taxfmt|Pyrus pyrifolia|species}})\n|[[Korean pear]] ({{taxfmt|Pyrus pyrifolia|species}})\n|Le Conte pear\n|Malvern pear|Moorcroft pear\n|nashi pear|Welsh pear\n|[[sand pear]] ({{taxfmt|Pyrus pyrifolia|species}}))|Seckel pear|[[snow pear]] ({{taxlink|Pyrus nivalis|species}})|{{vern|snowy pear}}|stinking bishop pear|[[strawberry pear]] ({{taxfmt|Stenocereus|genus}} (syn. {{taxfmt|Hylocereus|genus}}) spp.)|{{vern|sugar pear}}\n|[[Taiwan pear]], {{vern|Taiwanese pear}} ({{taxfmt|Pyrus pyrifolia|species}}))\n|[[vegetable pear]] ({{taxfmt|Sechium edule|species}})|{{vern|vine pear}}\n|{{vern|willowleaf pear}}, {{vern|willow-leafed pear}} ({{taxlink|Pyrus salicifolia|species}})\n}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en\n|alligator pear|and a partridge in a pear tree|apples and pears|avocado pear\n|butter pear\n|Catherine pear|choke pear\n|desert pear\n|ground pear\n|musk pear\n|papple\n|{{vern|pear apple}}\n|pear belle Hélène|{{vern|pear blight}}\n|pear cider\n|pear drop\n|pear-encrinite\n|pear-gauge,pear gauge\n|{{vern|pear haw}} ({{taxfmt|Crataegus|genus}} spp.)\n|pearita\n|Pearland|{{vern|pear leaf blister mite}} ({{taxlink|Eriophyes pyri|species}})|{{vern|pear leaf blister moth}} ({{taxlink|Leucoptera malifoliella|species}})|{{vern|pear leaf-curling midge}}, {{vern|pear leaf midge}}|pearless|pearlike|{{vern|pear louse}}\n|{{vern|pear midge}} ({{taxlink|Contarinia pyrivora|species}})|pearmonger\n|pear of anguish|pear orchard|{{vern|pear oyster scale}} ({{taxlink|Pseudaulacaspis pentagona|species}})\n|[[pear plum]]|[[pear psylla]] ({{taxlink|Psylla pyri|species}})\n|{{vern|pear quince}}\n|pear-shaped|{{vern|pear shell}}|[[pear slug]] ({{taxlink|Caliroa cerasi|species}})|pear-sucker\n|pear-thorn|[[pear thrips]] ({{taxlink|Taeniothrips inconsequens|species}})|peartini|pear tomato|pear tree,peartree|Pear Tree\n|pear wine|pear-wise|{{vern|pear-withe}}|pear-wood\n|peary\n|perry|Pope's pear|[[prickly pear]], [[prickly pear cactus]] ({{taxfmt|Opuntia|genus}} spp.)\n|river pear\n|sea pear\n|tiger pear\n|wax pear|wooden pear|woody pear\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n{{top3}}\n* {{desc|yue|啤梨|bor=1|der=1}}\n* {{desc|km|ផ្លែភា|bor=1|der=1}}\n* {{desc|st|pere|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|th|แพร์|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tkl|pea|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|xh|ipere|bor=1}}\n{{bottom}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|fruit}}\n* Abkhaz: {{t|ab|аҳа}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+|af|peer}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|dardhë|f}}\n* Apache:\n*: Jicarilla: {{t|apj|béela}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|كُمَّثْرَى|f}}, {{t|ar|إِجَّاص|m}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{t|arz|كمترة|f|tr=kummitra}} {{qualifier|collective}}, {{t|arz|كمتراية|f|tr=kummitrāya}} (''[[singulative]]'')\n*: Gulf Arabic: {{t|afb|عرموط|m|tr=ʕarmūṭ}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{t|acw|كُمِّثْرَى|f|tr=kummitra}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{t|ary|بوعويد|tr=buʕwīd}}, {{t|ary|إجاص|tr=ijjāṣ}}\n*: South Levantine Arabic: {{t|ajp|إنجاص|m|tr=injāṣ}}\n* Aragonese: {{t+|an|pera|f}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{t|aii