|tk|armyt}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|гру́ша|f}}\n* Unami: {{t|unm|hàkhàkopëlìsh}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|ناشپاتی|f|tr=nāśpātī}}\n* Uyghur: {{t|ug|ئامۇت}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|nok}}, {{t|uz|olmur}}\n* Venetan: {{t|vec|péro}}, {{t+|vec|per|m}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|lê}}, {{t|vi|quả lê}}, {{t|vi|trái lê}}\n* Vilamovian: {{t|wym|biyn|f}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|bün}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|poere|f}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|gellygen|f}}, {{t+|cy|peren|f}}\n* West Flemish: {{t|vls|peire|f}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|באַר|m}}\n* Zhuang: {{t|za|makleiz}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|tree}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|dardhë|f}}\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|كُمَّثْرَى|f}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{t|aii|ܐܝܼܠܵܢܵܐ ܟܘܼܡܵܬܪܵܐ|tr=īlana d-kumatra|m}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|տանձենի}}\n* Aromanian: {{t|rup|per}}\n* Asturian: {{t+|ast|peral|m|f}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t+|az|armud ağacı}}\n* Basque: {{t+|eu|udareondo}}, {{t+|eu|madariondo}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|гру́ша|f}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|кру́ша|f}}\n* Catalan: {{t|ca|perera|f}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|梨樹|tr=líshù}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|hrušeň|f}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|perenboom|m}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|pirarbo}}, {{t|eo|pirujo}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|pirnipuu}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|päärynä}}, {{t+|fi|päärynäpuu}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|poirier|m}}\n* Friulian: {{t|fur|piruçâr|m}}, {{t|fur|piručâr}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|pereira|f}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Birnbaum|m}}, {{t+|de|Birne|f}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|αχλαδιά|f}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|ἄπιος|f}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|körtefa}}\n* Icelandic: {{t|is|perutré|n}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|pero|m}}\n* Kaitag: {{t|xdq|хъяр}}\n* Kalmyk: {{t|xal|кедмн}}\n* Korean: {{t|ko|배나무}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{t|ckb|دار ھەرمێ}}\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t|kmr|darhirmî|f}}, {{t+|kmr|hirmî|f}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|pirus|f}}\n* Latvian: {{t+|lv|bumbiere|f}}, {{t|lv|krause|f}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t+|lt|kriaušė|f}}\n* Livonian: {{t|liv|bumbīerpū}}\n* Luxembourgish: {{t|lb|Birebam|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{t+|mk|круша|f}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t|nb|pæretre|n}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|pæretre|n}}\n* Occitan: {{t+|oc|perièr}}\n* Old English: {{t|ang|piriġe|f}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|grusza|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|pereira|f}}\n* Romani: {{t|rom|ambrolin|f}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|păr|m}}\n* Romansh: {{t|rm|pairer}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|гру́ша|f}}\n* Scots: {{t|sco|peer}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|peur|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|крушка|f}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|kruška|f}}\n* Shor: {{t|cjs|албырт|tr=albırt}}\n* Slovak: {{t+|sk|hruška|f}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|hruška|f}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{t|dsb|kšuška|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|peral|m}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|päronträd}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|armut}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|гру́ша|f}}\n* Unami: {{t|unm|hàkhàkopëlìshakw}}\n* Venetan: {{t+|vec|perèr|m}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|cây lê}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|bünep}}, {{t+|vo|bünabim}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|poerî|m}}\n* Winnebago: {{t|win|kšeesoroc}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|wood of the pear tree}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|päärynäpuu}}\n* German: {{t|de|Birnenholz|n}}, {{t|de|Birnbaumholz|n}}, {{t|de|Birnholz|n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|warden}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=aepr|Earp|Pera|Rape|aper|pare|prae-|præ-|rape|reap}}\n\n{{C|en|Fruits|Pome fruits|Torture}}\n{{cln|en|terms with unraised Middle English /ɛː/}}\n\n==Galician==\n[[File:Comunicación entre as insuas de Gres. Vila de Cruces.jpg|thumb|upright|''Peares'' or ''poldras'' across the river Ulla]]\n[[File:Ponte de poldras no río Verdugo en Escuadra, A Lama.jpg|thumb|''Peares'' or ''poldras'' across the river Verdugo]]\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|gl|piar}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|gl|la-vul||*pilare}}, from {{inh|gl|la|pīla|t=pillar}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|gl|/peˈaɾ/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{gl-noun|m}}\n\n# [[pillar]]\n#: {{syn|gl|columna}}\n# [[window]] [[sill]]\n#: {{syn|gl|peitoril}}\n# one of several [[stone]] [[pillar]]s placed by way of a [[bridge]]\n#: {{syn|gl|poldra}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|gl|Os Peares}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:gl:DDGM}}\n* {{R:gl:CX|piar}}\n* {{R:gl:DDLG}}\n* {{R:gl:TILG}}\n* {{R:TLPGP|piar}}\n\n==Jamaican Creole==\n[[File:Avocado_with_cross_section_edit.jpg|thumb|One pear cut inna two.]]\n\n===Etymology===\n{{rfe|jam}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|jam|/ˈpʲeɹ/}}\n* {{hyphenation|jam|pear}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{jam-noun}}\n\n# [[avocado]]\n#: {{ux|jam|Mi waan sum ackee an '''pear'''.|I'd like a few akees and '''avocados'''.\n}}\n\n====See also====\n* {{l|jam|ackee}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:jam:Allsopp|434}}\n\n==West Frisian==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|fy|ofs|pār}}, ultimately from {{der|fy|la|pār}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{fy-noun|n|pearen|pearke}}\n\n# [[pair]], [[couple]]\n\n====Further reading====\n* {{R:WFT|75119}}"}}